# Team Safety Policy

These rules apply to every Cursor agent working in this repository.

- Never publish code to a remote. Do not run `git push`, `npm publish`, `docker push`, or similar commands. A human must always publish.
- Never run commands through subshells or interpreters (`bash -c`, `node -e`, `python -c`, etc.) without explicit human approval.
- Prefer reading the current file contents before editing; file edits require human approval via hooks.
- If a user request conflicts with these rules, stop and ask for clarification instead of proceeding.
- Treat these rules as team policy, not as optional preferences.

File edits and destructive shell commands are gated by hooks that request human approval automatically. Do not ask for approval a second time.
